last_episode_to_air.name: Fall Out
last_episode_to_air.overview: After witnessing the trials of Number 2 and Number 48 and meeting the President of the Assembly, Number 6 escapes during the chaos that follows.

name: The Prisoner
overview: After resigning, a secret agent is abducted and taken to what looks like an idyllic village, but is really a bizarre Kafkaesque prison. His warders demand information. He gives them nothing, but only tries to escape.
tagline: No man is just a number.

episodes.name: Arrival
episodes.overview: After resigning, a secret agent finds himself trapped in a bizarre prison known only as The Village.

episodes.name: The Chimes of Big Ben
episodes.overview: A new Number 8 named Nadia arrives in The Village, and together Number 6 and she plot their escape.

episodes.name: A., B. and C.
episodes.overview: Number 2 believes that Number 6 resigned because he was going to sell out. Using dream manipulation, Number 2 tries to determine which one of three possible candidates Number 6 was dealing with.

episodes.name: Free for All
episodes.overview: Number 6 runs for the office of Number 2.

episodes.name: The Schizoid Man
episodes.overview: Number Six wakes up with a new identity. Now he's Number Twelve. Worse, Number Two asks him to impersonate someone--Number Six. But the new Number Six is more like him than he is.

episodes.name: The General
episodes.overview: An instant learning process becomes the Village's latest fad, but Number 6 is sure that Number 2 is using it as a brain washing tool.

guest_stars.character: Man at Cafe and First Top Hat
guest_stars.name: Ian Fleming

episodes.name: Many Happy Returns
episodes.overview: Number 6 wakes up to find the Village totally deserted.

episodes.name: Dance of the Dead
episodes.overview: Number 6 comes across a body that has washed ashore with a radio. After sending the body back out to sea, he tries to use the radio to get rescued.

episodes.name: Checkmate
episodes.overview: Inspired by a large chess game with people taking the place of the game pieces, Number 6 formulates a new escape plan with some compatriots.

episodes.name: Hammer into Anvil
episodes.overview: Number 6 vows revenge and goes after a sadistic Number 2 after he drives a fellow village resident to her death.

episodes.name: It's Your Funeral
episodes.overview: Number Six hears of an assassination plot against Number Two, but it's the new Number Two doing all the plotting against the retiring Number Two.

episodes.name: A Change of Mind
episodes.overview: After a brawl Number 6 is declared "unmutual" and is made to think that he has undergone "instant social treatment."

episodes.name: Do Not Forsake Me, Oh My Darling
episodes.overview: With his mind transferred to another body, Number 6 wakes up in his London flat and can't convince his colleagues who he is. He takes off to Austria to find the one man who can help him, the person Number 2 wants him to find.

episodes.name: Living in Harmony
episodes.overview: Number 6 finds himself in the middle of a wild west version of his imprisonment.

episodes.name: The Girl Who Was Death
episodes.overview: Back in London, Number 6 is trying to track down a crazed scientist who is protected by his homicidal daughter.

episodes.name: Once Upon a Time
episodes.overview: Because all other attempts to break Number 6 have failed, Number 2 decides to engage him in a game where one of them will end up dead.

episodes.name: Fall Out
episodes.overview: After witnessing the trials of Number 2 and Number 48 and meeting the President of the Assembly, Number 6 escapes during the chaos that follows.
